yingyinNormal.en: Cary, we don't decide until we vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 凯里，我们投票之后才能决定。

yingyinNormal.en: Shouldn't we all vote on stuff like this?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种事我们总要投票解决吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Ridiculous. Sheldon, I vote that is not a tangent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 太荒谬了。谢尔顿，我投票，这不是带偏题。

yingyinNormal.en: Granted, but Edmunds' data is more promising. We should vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有道理，但是Edmunds的数据前景更好。我们应该投票。

yingyinNormal.en: And when it got a vote earlier this year. Republicans flat-out voted "no".
yingyinNormal.zh: 当今年早些时候有一个投票的机会。共和党人断然投票反对。

yingyinNormal.en: We didn't vote. We didn't have to, that was clearly a tangent. Now come on. Back to work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们还没有投票呢。不必投票，你明显是带偏话题了，快点，继续工作。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm urging these governors to consolidate their polling sites and create quote, unquote "voting centers" so that people feel safe to come out and vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我督促这些州长合并投票站建立"投票中心"这样民众会觉得出门投票是安全的。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you flexing? I'm stalling until the House vote happens and then the Senate votes accordingly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在耍滑头吗？我想拖到众议院完成投票，好让参议院据结果投票。

yingyinNormal.en: Thank you. Thank you. We will now vote on the resolution. Ladies and gentlemen, please cast your vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢各位。谢谢，现在就方案进行表决，女士们，先生们，请投票。

yingyinNormal.en: I think it'll be pretty clear. If not, we'll take a vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想很容易判断吧，如果模棱两可就投票决定。

yingyinNormal.en: We want to assure anyone who's considering not voting that it is not only safe to vote, it is your duty to do so.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们希望任何在考虑不投票的各位知道现在投票不仅是安全的，更是你们的责任。

yingyinNormal.en: And whether they vote for me or not, I have to lead them as well.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不管他们是不是为我投票，我也得带领他们。

yingyinNormal.en: The vote isn't until tomorrow afternoon. I'll reach out to Mendoza.
yingyinNormal.zh: 明天下午才开始投票，我一早就会联系Mendoza。

yingyinNormal.en: So that's how it'll be? Fight to the death? No. We vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以这就是事情的发展方向吗？针锋相对，互不相让吗？不，我们投票。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm a partner. You want to remove me, you need the majority vote of the executive board, and then you need a vote of the full board.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是个合伙人，你想开除我，你需要执行委员会的多数票，然后你需要正式合伙人投票。

yingyinNormal.en: First of all, the vote is never gonna get to the Senate. It's a senseless partisan circus.
yingyinNormal.zh: 首先，投票就不会进入参议院。这只是毫无意义的党争闹剧。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm here to ask a favor. I want you to call for a vote. Project Insight has to be delayed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我来找你帮个忙，我想请你发动一次投票，洞察计划必须得推迟。

yingyinNormal.en: The House is about to vote, Donald. What is going on? Let's get this done so you can go home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 众议院即将投票，唐纳德。怎么回事？我们把这事弄完，你就能回家了。

yingyinNormal.en: Move the anti-filibuster measure forward so the Senate can vote and elect me vice president. No. No?
yingyinNormal.zh: 推进抗阻挠措施，好让参议院能投票选我担任副总统。不行。不行？

yingyinNormal.en: Well, if we're going to vote, there's something you should know. Brand? He has a right to know.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，要是投票的话，有件事你应该要知道，Brand，他有权知道。

sense_info_list.en: express one's views in response to a poll, especially to exercise a political franchise

examination_example.sentence: In France, shareholders who hold onto a company investment for at least two years can sometimes earn more <highlight>voting</highlight> rights in a company.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在法国，持有公司投资至少两年的股东有时可以获得更多的公司投票权。

examination_example.sentence: With Britain <highlight>voting</highlight> to leave the European Union, GDP already predicted to slow as a result.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着英国投票决定离开欧盟，预计GDP将因此放缓。

examination_example.sentence: Enraged by Entergy's behavior, the Vermont Senate <highlight>voted</highlight> 26 to 4 last year against allowing an extension.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 被Entergy的行为激怒的佛蒙特州参议院去年以26票对4票否决了延期。

sense_info_list.en: a formal choice that you make in an election or at a meeting in order to choose someone or decide something

examination_example.sentence: On a five to three <highlight>vote</highlight>, the Supreme Court knocked out much of Arizona's immigration law Monday.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最高法院星期一以五比三的票数否决了亚利桑那州大部分移民法。

examination_example.sentence: Its current leader, Ed Miliband, owes his position to <highlight>votes</highlight> from public-sector unions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 工党现任领袖Ed Miliband的地位要归功于公共部门工会的选票。

word_usage.usage:
vote用作及物动词时可接名词、代词或that从句作宾语，也可接双宾语。例：
The directors have just voted themselves a huge pay increase.
董事们刚刚投票同意给他们自己大幅度提高工资。

vote against sb./sth.投票反对；vote for sb./sth.投……的票；投票支持……；vote on sth.就……表决。例：
Did you vote for or against her? 
你投了她的赞成票还是反对票
They took a vote on who should go first. 
他们以投票方式决定谁先走。
